# How to get your Google Client ID

To enable the "Auto-Unlock" feature, you need a Google Client ID. Follow these steps:

1.  **Go to Google Cloud Console**: [https://console.cloud.google.com/](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2.  **Create a Project**:
    - Click on the project dropdown at the top left.
    - Click "New Project" and name it "TV Time App".
3.  **Enable Gmail API**:
    - In the search bar at the top, type "Gmail API".
    - Click "Gmail API" from the results and click **"Enable"**.
4.  **Configure OAuth Consent Screen**:
    - Click the Hamburg Menu (☰) -> **APIs & Services** -> **OAuth consent screen**.
    - Select **"External"** and click **Create**.
    - Fill in "App name" (TV Time App), "User support email" (your email), and "Developer contact information" (your email). Click **Save and Continue**.
    - Click "Add or Remove Scopes" and add `.../auth/gmail.readonly`. Click **Save and Continue**.
    - **Crucial Step: Add Test Users**:
        - Click **+ Add Users**.
        - Enter **`lakshveeronline@gmail.com`** and click **Add**.
    - Click **Save and Continue** until the end.
5.  **Create Credentials**:
    - Click the Hamburg Menu (☰) -> **APIs & Services** -> **Credentials**.
    - Click **+ Create Credentials** -> **OAuth client ID**.
    - Select **"Web application"** for Application Type.
    - Under **Authorized JavaScript origins**, click "Add URI" and enter:
      `http://localhost:8000`
    - Under **Authorized redirect URIs**, click "Add URI" and enter:
      `http://localhost:8000`
    - Click **Create**.
6.  **Copy the Client ID**:
    - You will see a popup with "Your Client ID". It looks like a long string of numbers and letters ending in `.apps.googleusercontent.com`.
